to the editor isisara bey who works in the music division of sony insists that a persuasive reason for presenting a prestigious literary award to stephen king is that his books make really great movies arts pages sept 15 but is n't it axiomatic that action filled novels lacking subtlety often make commercially successful films while complex fiction invariably comes to grief on the screen moreover are n't great movies and laugh tracked television comedies among the reasons so few americans read serious literature and is n't it literacy after all and not popular entertainment that the national book foundation is or should be all about joel conarroe new york sept 15 2003 the writer was chairman of the national book foundation 1991 93

